Welcome to the Vox Book Club’s second week of discussion on N.K.
As with last week’s discussion, there will be no spoilers for the end of the book in the main post.
And in some ways, that’s because of the very diversity and community that The City We Became celebrates.
That’s what’s hiding in the Alt Artiste painting, and that’s what really makes the Woman in White dangerous.
Granted, we’ve only had limited access to the primary so far, but I have to ask: Do you ship it?